createLoginSession

public LoginSession createLoginSession(org.apache.wicket.Request r)
Create a LoginSession object in the database based on the current Session and the given Request. This should generally be called when a user logs in. Many details about the client and session will be filled in automatically if you put this in your Application's init() method: getRequestCycleSettings().setGatherExtendedBrowserInfo(true); (see the javadoc for ClientProperties).

Parameters:
r - the current Request object
Returns:
the created LoginSession

forceCloseLoginSession

public void forceCloseLoginSession(org.hibernate.Session dbSession,
                                   LoginSession loginSession,
                                   String comment)
Closes a LoginSession without a logout - timeout or server shutdown. This will also save an event.

Note: Since this is called from shutdown hooks, a regular Databinder session may not be available. Therefore, a Databinder session must be passed in. This method will NOT commit any changes or handle any transactions. The session transaction must be flushed after this method is called.

Parameters:
dbSession - a Hibernate session to use
loginSession - the LoginSession to be closed
comment - added to the event detail field

getEventTypes

getLastEventTime

public Date getLastEventTime(LoginSession ls)
Get the date of most recent event in a LoginSession. Use sparingly; this requires a database query across all events in the LoginSession.
